<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="650" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/2575: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-23T19:00:00-05:00">December 23, 1932—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>81. Your No. 136 of December 21, 1 [<hi rend="italic">3?</hi>] p.m. To
                            date the bankers have not submitted to the Department the proposal
                            regarding a short time advance outlined by De la Rue. The Department as
                            at present advised sees no reason to modify its view regarding an
                            increase in the public debt as stated in the last sentence of
                            telegraphic instruction No. 79 of December 17, 2 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>